89
00:05:47.940 --> 00:05:51.460
corepressor, NURD, or mitotic deacetylase.

90
00:05:51.840 --> 00:05:55.460
So if you hit one enzyme, for example, the HDAC1 or 2,

91
00:05:55.880 --> 00:05:59.490
you're not just perturbing the enzyme, you are hitting and

92
00:05:59.560 --> 00:06:01.600
disrupting all of these complexes.

93
00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:05.820
And as a consequence, thousands of genes are de-repressed

94
00:06:05.980 --> 00:06:09.480
all at once. So this is not a mere side

95
00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:12.572
effect.So you are causing a lot of

96
00:06:12.612 --> 00:06:14.992
cytotoxicity and off-target effect,

97
00:06:15.872 --> 00:06:19.652
because of which we have so less clinical success with the

98
00:06:19.672 --> 00:06:21.592
traditional enzymatic inhibitors.

99
00:06:22.312 --> 00:06:26.072
Now, can we shift the paradigm from enzymatic to non-enzymatic

100
00:06:26.152 --> 00:06:30.132
inhibitors? That is, instead of targeting the whole HDAC1

101
00:06:30.172 --> 00:06:33.632
or 2, we try to target specific protein-protein

102
00:06:33.712 --> 00:06:37.232
interfaces that is bringing the whole complex together.

103
00:06:38.412 --> 00:06:42.372
Now, before we move forward to the experimental design, a few word

104
00:06:42.431 --> 00:06:46.312
