109
00:07:00.552 --> 00:07:04.012
Rpd3 is the yeast ortholog of human HDAC1

110
00:07:04.032 --> 00:07:07.392
and 2, which is the main histone

111
00:07:07.472 --> 00:07:10.332
acetylase. It's very well known as HDAC1 and 2.

112
00:07:12.092 --> 00:07:15.472
Then you have Ume6. It's a

113
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:19.692
sequence-specific transcription factor, and this recruits this

114
00:07:19.752 --> 00:07:22.932
complex. And once this is recruited, so this

115
00:07:23.392 --> 00:07:27.332
represses genes such as URA3, and without

116
00:07:27.432 --> 00:07:29.592
uracil, yeast cannot practically grow.

117
00:07:30.112 --> 00:07:33.632
Now, exploiting this biology, we built this cell-based

